@NODE "desc" "Description of program"

                    A Description of what JumpED is and does
                    ----------------------------------------

      JumpED is a tool i wrote because of those times when you load up an
         old source code you wrote and then think where the hell's that
      function gone ! , and you can't quite remember it's name to use your
                          Editors Search function :-\\

    Basically JumpED reads through an ascii file and then presents you with
                           a list of all functions..

               Clicking one of these Items then makes your editor
                     Jump to the line denoted in the list.

            By Default JumpED recognises the following filetypes...

      ARexx(Fallback type), Amiga_E, AmigaGuide, Javascript/php, Perl/CGI


                More filetypes can be added in the preferences.

       A filetype not listed will be searched for ARexx type definitions
              ie. the 1st word of a line ends in a ':' character.
            eg. this readme will load and list all the paragraphs :)


                    Multiple Editors can also be added/used.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "usag" "How to use"

                                     Usage:
                                     ------

   double click WB icon or run with no args to load a doc via file requester
                         or execute 'JumpED <Filename>'

                   For a full list of arguments @{" Click Here " LINK "args"}

        You double click a list item and your editor will automatically
                         jump to the right line number.

     you can enter a new name in the string gadget to specify another doc.
         also window is an app window so you can drop an icon onto it.


Bottom right there is a popup gadget for a
list with the following functions...

Re-Read File   ; This will read / re-read the document
Search for Line; Open the Find window
Configuration  ; See @{" Settings " LINK "sett"}
Change Editor  ; use a different editor
Quit JumpED    ; erm
@ENDNODE

@NODE "sett" "Configuration"

                                   Settings:
                                   ---------

             JumpED is set up best to use BED or TurboText as their
         ARexx commands are practically identical and i know BED well.

      It also has defaults for GoldED and DigitalQuill but as i do not use
    these i haven't made them perfect but you can edit the commands used for
      jumping to suit your own editor, you must know it's ARexx commands.

     The BED/TTX Settings may look a bit complicated to the novice but set
    up this way I can run JumpED at any time (even if doc or ed are closed)

                  The Jump setting is simply an ARexx function

           IF YOU GET THIS TO WORK WITH OTHER EDITORS OR IMPROVE THE
        SETTINGS IN ANY WAY , PLEASE SEND ME YOUR envarc:JumpED.ini file
                         SO I CAN UPGRADE THE SUPPORT.

                                     THANKS


Here is the default arexx command for BED

note: I use @{b}%f@{ub} to add the filename and @{b}%n@{ub} for the line number

-----------------------
/* Check BED is running and load with doc if not */
if ~show(p,'BED') then do
 address command
 'run >nil: BED "%f"'
 'waitforport BED_0'
 address value 'BED_0'
end

 /* or bed is open so we check doc is loaded */
else do
 address 'BED'
 getdocuments
 docs=result; fp='%f'
 name=substr(fp,max(lastpos('/',fp),lastpos(':',fp))+1)
 if index(docs,name)==0 then opendoc fp
 Getport name; port=RESULT
 address value port
end

/* Move to the function line */
move %n CENTER
activatewindow
-----------------------


The 'Page' Cycle toggles the Main or Editor settings.

   'Save' saves settings to env: and envarc:
    'Use' saves settings to env: only
'Reload' restores settings from Envarc:
 'Cancel' Closes Prefs Window
-----------------------

Jump On:
--------
Double Click only:  list must be double clicked to jump
Double & Single Click: jumps on single clicks

Show Line Numbers:
------------------
This Checkmark will toggle the showing of the
line numbers in the main list.



Supported File Type Settings:
-----------------------------

Here you add / edit / remove supported file types.

FileTypes are recognised by their extentions.

Rules for a line can be.....

Before:
 Text must be before the function name.

After:
 Text must be after the function name.

Quotes:
 Tick if the name might be more than 1 word in quotes
 like the Guide type.

Match Case:
 Case refers to the Before / After matching.

 Unchecked; foo is FOO
 Checked  ; foo is not FOO

----------------------------------------


