@NODE cata "Catalog Support"


JumpED has FULL Catalog support

No Languages have been submitted yet but if you want your
language included then read below...

YOU MUST READ THE "RULES" BELOW


How to add catalogs for your own language.
------------------------------------------

PLEASE READ THIS...   (And See the RULES Below)

The method used by me is using a program found on Aminet called SimpleCat

get SimpleCat from aminet and put it in your c: dir
@{" Click here to Download SimpleCat " RXS "call addlib('openurl.library',3,-66); call OpenURL('http://uk.aminet.net/pub/aminet/dev/misc/simplecat.lha', SHOW, TOFRONT, LAUNCH)"}


SimpleCat is very easy to use as all args are already set in the .cs file

the '.cs' files are the descriptor files for use with SimpleCat.

languages are defined on the first line seperated by commas ','

eg.
## languages english,deutsch,espańol

then the Locale Strings are defined by line and seperated by ';'
eg.

MSG_YES
_Yes
_Ya
_Si
;
MSG_HELLO
Hello
Hallo
Bonjour
;


it is best to edit the catalogs in the original archive Catalog dir.
I have included a little dos script that will run SimpleCat
(SimpleCat MUST be in your path eg. C:SimpleCat)



RULES:
------

PLEASE TRY TO STICK TO THESE RULES IN MAKING TRANSLATIONS...
------------------------------------------------------------

Please Please try to keep all texts to a similar length
larger texts will affect the sizes of the gui/gadgets and requesters

This is MORE important with Gadgets than Messages.

if possible use Abreviations to try to make the gui smaller.

Watch out for the special characters like \e1 \ec as they are used by mui
Watch out for _Underscores , ensure you don't repeat keykodes to gadgets


PLEASE Send me your updated ".cs" files and docs (if you made docs),

NO OTHER FILES WILL BE ACCEPTED OR USED

@{" Bruce Steers <bsteers@ukonline.co.uk> " RXS "call addlib('openurl.library',3,-66); call OpenURL('mailto:bsteers@ukonline.co.uk?SUBJECT=JumpED Catalogs', SHOW, TOFRONT, LAUNCH)"}


Thanks for reading this Text,
Bruce


-------------------------------------------
ONLY SEND ME EDITED .cs FILES (and/or docs)
-------------------------------------------

I WILL NOT accept any .catalog or any other translation methods

you are free upload a catalog to aminet but be aware that if
i add/remove any strings then your catalogs won't work but if
i have the .cs file they will :)

Submitters of languages will definetly have
their names Added above :)


@ENDNODE

