@NODE "args" "Arguments"
@NOWORDWRAP
Jumped has 3 args...

Syntax: JumpED FILE,QUICK/S,ED/K

@{b}FILE@{ub}
Set a filename to open on launch

example:
@{b}JumpED sys:tools/JumpED.guide@{ub}

-----

@{b}QUICK@{ub}
Use QUICK to make JumpED quit when the list is doubleClicked
Usefull if you want to only use it once then quit.

example:
@{b}JumpED sys:tools/JumpED.guide quick@{ub}

-----

@{b}ED@{ub}
Use an alternative editor to the fallback one
Usefull for launching from the said editor.
Name is the same as in the settings (case-insensitive)

example:
@{b}JumpED sys:tools/JumpED.guide ED golded@{ub}

-----

Launching Example:

You could save the following as a BED:rexx/Jumped.bed and add it to
BEDs menus using @{b}ExecArexxMacro "BED:rexx/jumped.bed"@{ub}
@{b}
OPTIONS RESULTS
GETFILEPATH
file=RESULT
address command 'run >nil: sys:tools/JumpED ED BED 'file"
@{ub}

Note:
The above can also be bunched up as a BED menu item with KeyCode "J"
(note: this should be a sngle line but wordwrapping will wrap it)
@{b}
ITEM  "JumpED" "J" ExecARexxString CONSOLE "OPTIONS RESULTS; GETFILEPATH; file=RESULT; address command 'run >nil: sys:tools/JumpED ED BED 'file"
@{ub}

@ENDNODE

